Synopsis:
   set status_umode [<text>]

Description:
   This variable contains the string used in the status bar when the client
   has one or more user modes set.  If no user modes are set, nothing is
   displayed.

   This string is represented at %# in the STATUS_FORMAT string.  If the
   expando is used inside STATUS_UMODE, it expands to the client's current
   user mode.

Examples:
   Customizing the display of the current user mode in the status bar:
      /set status_umode UserMode: %#

See Also:
   mode(1); set(4) status_format

